SIMPLE: embowel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embowel
<hw>Em*bow"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Emboweled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr> or
<conjf>Embowelled</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Emboweling</conjf> or <conjf>Embowelling</conjf>.]</vmorph>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To disembowel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The barbarous practice of <qex>emboweling</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The boar . . . makes his trough⟦br⟧
In your <qex>emboweled</qex> bosoms.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Disembowel</xex> is the preferable word in this
sense.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To imbed; to hide in the inward parts; to
bury.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or deep <qex>emboweled</qex> in the earth entire.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emboweler</ent>⟦br⟧
